issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When comparing using ```comparingOnlyFields``` with mistyped field name, the assertion pass.

* assertj core version: 3.24.2
* java version: 17.0.8.1

**Example**

```java
public class AssertJTest implements WithAssertions {
    static class A1 {
        public final int a, b;
        public A1(int a, int b) {
            this.a = a;
            this.b = b;
        }
    }

    @Test
    public void testComparingOnly() {
        A1 a1 = new A1(1, 2);
        A1 a2 = new A1(3, 4);

        // This passes if we specify a non-existent field
        assertThat(a1).usingRecursiveComparison()
                .comparingOnlyFields("xxx")
                .isEqualTo(a2);
    }
}

```

**Describe the bug**
From version 3.25.0, it seems that method `usingRecursiveFieldByFieldElementComparatorOnFields` on `AbstractIterableAssert` returns an error if one of the fields don't exist. The problem is that I have polymorphic objects.

* assertj core version: 3.25.0
* java version: 21
* test framework version: junit 5.11.4
* os (if relevant): 

**Test case reproducing the bug**

Add a test case showing the bug that we can run

```java

@Data
@SuperBuilder
public abstract sealed class AppliedExemptionResponse permits AppliedTotalExemptionResponse, AppliedPartialExemptionResponse {
	String exemptionCode;
	String description;
	String chargeItemCode;
	String description;
}

@Value
@SuperBuilder
public class AppliedTotalExemptionResponse extends AppliedExemptionResponse {
}

@Value
@SuperBuilder
public class AppliedPartialExemptionResponse extends AppliedExemptionResponse {
	BigDecimal value;
	String type;
	boolean replacement;
}

public class MyTest {

	@Test
	void test() {

		final List<AppliedExemptionResponse> appliedExemptions = List.of(
				AppliedTotalExemptionResponse.builder().exemptionCode( "E1" ).build(),
				AppliedPartialExemptionResponse.builder().value( BigDecimal.ZERO ).build()
		);
		final List<AppliedExemptionResponse> expectedAppliedExemptions = List.of(
				AppliedTotalExemptionResponse.builder().exemptionCode( "E1" ).build(),
				AppliedPartialExemptionResponse.builder().value( BigDecimal.ZERO ).build()
		);

		assertThat( appliedExemptions )
				.usingRecursiveFieldByFieldElementComparatorOnFields( "exemptionCode", "chargeItemCode", "description", "value" )
				.containsExactlyInAnyOrderElementsOf( expectedAppliedExemptions );
	}
}
```

The test fails with the following error:

`java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: The following fields don't exist: {value}`

How can I fix the problem?
